4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING AN INCOME TAX CREDIT FOR CERTAIN LONG-
5 TIME RESIDENTS OF THE STATE; PROVIDING AN INCOME LIMIT; PROVIDING A DEFINITION;
6 AMENDING SECTION 15-30-2303, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Montana 10-year resident credit. (1) A taxpayer who has resided in the
11 state for the prior 10 years and who has income of less than $100,000 is allowed a credit against the tax
12 imposed by 15-30-2103.
13 (2) A taxpayer is considered to have resided in Montana each year that the taxpayer resided in the
14 state for at least 7 months of the year.
15 (3) The amount of the credit allowed under this section is $500.
16 (4) The credit may not be refunded and may not be carried to another tax year.
17 (5) Pursuant to 5-4-104, the legislature finds that the purpose of the tax credit provided for in this
18 section is to reduce the tax burden of long-time Montana residents.
19 (6) For the purposes of this section, "income" has the same meaning as provided in 15-30-2337.
